    {
      "id": "7c078f43f143e992762d1714a72a6c7f0fad81a7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 19:07:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(12 inline comments)\n\nI'm in support of moving in this direction, but we need to work out some of the details before this patch can land.\n\nIf we are adding a separate build system for the kernel, I'd prefer that there be some plan in place to move to build all client packages using this new system so that it is definitely an _improved_ build system rather than just an _additional_ build system.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "30d8361f33ae9c07b8acb7d8683ca1911ad94cf8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 19:58:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nToro has started the test process",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "81fb7268e208a968709814482303d32671896c6d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 07:40:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (5 inline comments)\n\nAndreas, the patch only adds kbuild support for client kernel modules. Are you suggesting that we should extract all client code (modules, liblustre, utils) and have them build separately?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ff5a70d79421bd22cf3e73e75855eef3de679511",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-19 22:08:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHmm, I thought the build-client-source.sh script was extracting all of the files from a lustre master tree and moving them to their appropriate location in the linux kernel tree?\n\nWhat I'm hoping to see is the ability to \"regenerate\" the client code from the Lustre master to the form that it is currently in the kernel, so that \"diff\" can be run on it and see what changes are missing from each codebase.  The easier that this is done, the easier it will be to see which patches are missing and need to be ported one way or the other.  Otherwise, we have to keep track of this by hand, and it is error prone.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "60d03ee02a949babb084aa1f85088f92a081db45",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 179,
        "name": "Peng Tao",
        "email": "bergwolf@gmail.com",
        "username": "bergwolf"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-20 05:55:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nbuild/build-client-source.sh only extract lustre client kernel code from master into lustre-client directory.\n\nThe other script build/copy-builtin is used to copy all client code from lustre-client directory into a kernel tree, and add corresponding Kconfigs and Makefiles.\n\nI split them so that these two functionalities can be reviewed/maintained independently.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "016a65af90877148bbec6436acd950acf459d8f7",
      "author": {
